ntly change. <b>Conclusions:</b> This lifestyle intervention may be an effective means for improving body mass index in primary school children in the short-term if the duration of the intervention is increased, but these changes may not be sustained without on-going support.', 'original': None}", 'Authors': "[{'first_name': 'Elise C.', 'last_name': 'Brown', 'initials': None, 'researcher_id': 'ur.012567702501.05', 'grid_ids': array(['grid.261277.7'], dtype=object), 'orcid': array(['0000-0002-2584-0052'], dtype=object), 'corresponding': True, 'raw_affiliations': array(['Department of Public and Environmental Wellness, Oakland University, Rochester, MI, United States'],
