l rig. The combined numerical and experimental approach is used to predict significant losses produced during various operating conditions. It is shown that cavitation becomes significant at low temperatures due to micro-hydrodynamic action, enhanced by high fluid viscosity. The magnitude of the losses for these components under various operating conditions is presented. The combined numerical-experimental study of wet multi-plate brakes of off-highway vehicles with cavitation flow dynamics has not hitherto been reported in the literature.', 'original': None}", 'Authors': "[{'first_name': 'M', 'last_name': 'Leighton', 'initials': None, 'researcher_id': 'ur.012134104007.15', 'grid_ids': array(['grid.6571.5'], dtype=object), 'orcid': array(['0000-0002-9488-4999'], dtype=object), 'corresponding': False, 'raw_affiliations': array(['Wolfson School of Mechanical, Electrical and Manufacturing Engineering, Loughborough University, Loughborough, UK'],
