 bonding in other populations. Furthermore, associations between changes in closeness and both affect and anxiety support previous research suggesting associations between closeness, bonding, and wider mental health.', 'original': None}", 'Authors': "[{'first_name': 'Daisy', 'last_name': 'Fancourt', 'initials': None, 'researcher_id': 'ur.0615054541.73', 'grid_ids': array(['grid.83440.3b', 'grid.7445.2'], dtype=object), 'orcid': array(['0000-0002-6952-334X'], dtype=object), 'corresponding': False, 'raw_affiliations': array(['Department of Behavioural Science and Health, University College London, London, UK',
